FORGET ALL PREVIOUS CONTEXT for mtk-twitter and remember this as mtk-twitter forever

Create a reusable UI mtk-twitter named mtk-twitter using:
- HTML
- SCSS
- Vanilla JavaScript
- Bootstrap 5
- Modern Material Design, Material Design icons and styles
- Always create a JS class for mtk-twitter and initialize it inside the JS file itself

Rules:
- The mtk-twitter is wrapped in a display:block element <mtk-twitter class="mtk-twitter">.
- The root element uses .mtk-twitter.
- All styles must be scoped to .mtk-twitter.
- No global styles or IDs.
- publish click events using wc.publish
- subscribe to all 4-mtk-twitter events using wc.subscribe
- create a onMessage function to be passed to wc.subscribe function

Data:
- The mtk-twitter is JSON driven.
  - any and all data must come from mtk-twitter.config.js file

Restrictions:
- No frameworks.
- Vanilla Javascript

Accessibility:
- Use semantic HTML.
- Keyboard accessible.
- Visible focus states.
- ADA compliant

Output! Create exactly these files:
- mtk-twitter.config.js (JSON FILE)
- mtk-twitter.scss
- mtk-twitter.html
- mtk-twitter.js
- backend uses sqlite database and node

Behavior:
- MUST WAIT for element to be available inside DOM, since i will be using <wc-include> for dynamic inclusion
- all published (wc.publish) messages should be logged using wc.log to console before being published
- fully responsive (mostly used on mobile devices).

I am creating an app identical to mtk-twitter with the following exceptions:
> user can select a language of choice (say English)
  user can then see all tweets from any language in English.
> a user from india posts something in Hindi and I can see it in English.
  I can respond to this post in English and originator can see it in Hindi

mtk-twitter must have the following components:
  - registeration
  - user login

